article.description: Newell leads UT Martin over Austin Peay 76-64
article.headline: Newell leads UT Martin over Austin Peay 76-64
article.linkText: Newell leads UT Martin over Austin Peay 76-64
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- Marshun Newell hit two career highs with 23 points and 17 rebounds to lead UT Martin over Austin Peay 76-64 on Thursday night. Newell had 14 of UT Martin's 29 points at the half and shot 4 of 5 from distance. Alex Anderson added 19 points on 50-percent shooting. The Governors (7-16, 2-7 Ohio Valley Conference) were behind 29-24 at intermission but a slow start in the second -- just two points in the first six minutes -- had them trailing by 20 points. Austin Peay slowly climbed back from the deficit and five points from Chris Horton in an 8-1 run made it 68-60 with 1:20 to play. The Skyhawks (14-8, 6-3) shot 8 of 8 at the line in the final minute and Austin Peay missed four 3-pointers to end it. Josh Robinson finished with 15 points and Horton added 14 for the Governors.
